First, we can factor the numerator and denominator:
\[\frac{|x^2 - 81|}{(x - 6)(x - 6x)} = \frac{|x^2 - 81|}{(x - 6)^2}.\]Since the numerator is the absolute value of a nonnegative quantity, the fraction is nonnegative when $x$ is negative.  Also, the denominator is always positive, so we have
\[|x^2 - 81| < (x - 6)^2.\]If $x < 0,$ then $x^2 - 81 < 0,$ so $|x^2 - 81| = -(x^2 - 81) = 81 - x^2.$  Then $81 - x^2 < (x - 6)^2,$ which simplifies to $x^2 + 6x - 45 < 0.$  This quadratic factors as $(x + 9)(x - 5) < 0.$  The quadratic is negative for $-9 < x < 5,$ so we have $-9 < x < 0.$

If $x \ge 0,$ then $x^2 - 81 \ge 0.$  Then
\[\frac{|x^2 - 81|}{(x - 6)^2} = \frac{x^2 - 81}{(x - 6)^2},\]so this fraction is nonnegative when $x$ is nonnegative.  We can factor the numerator as $x^2 - 81 = (x - 9)(x + 9).$  Then
\[\frac{(x - 9)(x + 9)}{(x - 6)^2} < 0.\]The numerator is zero when $x = -9$ or $x = 9.$  The denominator is always positive, so we have
\[\frac{(x - 9)(x + 9)}{(x - 6)^2} < 0\quad\text{if and only if}\quad x = 9.\]Thus, the solution set is $\boxed{(-9,0) \cup (0,9)}.$พรีเมียร์ลีก

